title.rendered: Sydney vs Brisbane, Australian T20 League, 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Sydney: Josh Philippe (wk), Steven Smith, Kurtis Patterson, Moises Henriques (c), Jordan Silk, Hayden Kerr, Daniel Christian, Ben Dwarshuis, Sean Abbott, Steve O’Keefe, Izharulhaq Naveed

Brisbane: Usman Khawaja (c), Josh Brown, Marnus Labuschagne, Matt Renshaw, Sam Hain, Jimmy Peirson (wk), James Bazley, Michael Neser, Xavier Bartlett, Spencer Johnson, Matthew Kuhnemann

Venue: Sydney Cricket Ground, Sydney

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 162

2nd innings average score: 107

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Chasing has been challenging

Wins

Batting 1st: 100%

Batting 2nd: —

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Sean Abbott loves playing at the SCG. In only 44 games, he has bagged 72 wickets. His last three figures at the ground read 3 for 11, 3 for 18, and 2 for 17.

At the SCG, Steve O’Keefe has taken 38 wickets, including 3 four-wicket hauls. Incidentally, his last four-for came in the previous game against Thunder.

Steven Smith is the only batter from Sydney to feature in the Ultimate Team for 5 games in a row. His highest score 125* of the season came at the SCG.

Josh Philippe has encouraging numbers at his home ground. He has accumulated 788 runs at 34, including 9 half-centuries.

In 8 games against Sydney, Michael Neser has taken 12 wickets, including consecutive three-fors.

Only 23 sixes have been hit at the venue in the last 3 games, out of which Steven Smith has alone blasted 11.

In the same period, 9 out of 24 top-order batters have been dismissed in the single-digits.
